#!/var/lib/wireguardrtc/venv/bin/python3
"""wireguardrtc — WireGuard NAT hole-punching via PeerJS signalling.

Maintains direct UDP tunnels between WireGuard peers behind cone NATs by:

  - resolving the local public IPv4 via STUN
  - exchanging encrypted endpoint info via a (possibly-untrusted) PeerJS broker,
    using the standard PeerJS OFFER wire format
  - opening a NAT pinhole via raw UDP injection from the WG listen port
  - waking the kernel WG module to fire a handshake immediately

Configuration:

  /etc/wireguardrtc/wireguardrtc.conf   global daemon settings
  /etc/wireguardrtc/peers.d/*.conf      per-peer drop-in files (one per pubkey)

Peers without a drop-in file are ignored. See wg-holepunch-guide.md for details.
"""

